Pepper OpenPose / MediaPipe Teleoperation
=========================================

This project includes software from multiple sources. The Python teleoperation
code in this repository is licensed under the Apache License 2.0 (see LICENSE).

Third-party components (separate licenses — not included in this repo)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

- SoftBank Robotics Choregraphe Suite 2.5 — provides NAOqi Python bindings (`qi`, `naoqi`).
  Requires a SoftBank Robotics Community account and acceptance of their terms.
- SoftBank Pepper robot — hardware and NAOqi OS governed by SoftBank / vendor terms.
- Google MediaPipe — Apache License 2.0 (installed via pip for the body tracker).
- OpenCV — Apache License 2.0 (installed via pip).
- NumPy, SciPy, Matplotlib, PyZMQ, Pillow — per their respective PyPI licenses.
- Unity Engine and XR packages — Unity Software License (if you use the VR client).
- Optional: Microsoft Azure Kinect SDK and Body Tracking SDK (if using `azure_body_tracker.py`).

Inherited baseline
------------------

Parts of `pepper_teleoperation/` derive from an earlier Pepper teleoperation
codebase (2019, Apache 2.0). This repository extends that stack with MediaPipe
tracking, VR integration, and lab-specific documentation.
